   <category name='contract'>

      <section name='nothing'>

         <para number='1' comment='work/workboard/job/cargo/haul'>
         What you do to earn a living in the game varies from rank to rank. New players haul cargo around the Solar System. Cargo jobs are offered on the workboard - type 'WORK' to see the jobs currently available. You can be notified whenever new jobs are posted onto the workboard by typing 'JOBS ON' - turn the notifications off again with 'JOBS OFF'.
         </para>

         <para number='2'>
         For each job you are given the following information:
         </para>

         <para number='3'>
         The job number.
         </para>

         <para number='4'>
         The planet where the cargo is, and the destination planet. If you're still a Commander, make sure you only accept jobs to and from Solar System planets. To find out which planets are in Sol, see the map at http://www.ibgames.net/fed2/maps/solmap.html - scroll down to see the asteroid belt - or you can type 'DI SYSTEM SOL' to get a list of Sol planets.
         </para>

         <para number='5'>
         The size of the job, in tons - newbods start with 75 ton cargo holds so you can't carry larger jobs.
         </para>

         <para number='6'>
         The commodity you will be carrying.
         </para>

         <para number='7'>
         The time allowed, in galactic time units - one move in space equals 1 gtu. Ground moves don't count.
         </para>

         <para number='8'>
         The payment you will receive for the job, in groats per ton.
         </para>

         <para number='9'>
         The hauling credits you will receive, which you need for promotion.
         </para>

         <para number='10'>
         To bid for a job, the command is 'AC job#' - for example, 'AC 3' for job number 3 on the board. Jobs are awarded to the first bidder. If you get a job, the details show on your ship's status - type 'ST'.
         </para>

         <para number='11'>
         To carry out the job, go to the Armstrong Cuthbert office on the 'from' planet and type 'COLLECT', then go to the Armstrong Cuthbert office on the 'to' planet and type 'DELIVER'. If you decide you don't want to do the job, type 'VOID' - but you will be fined.
         </para>

         <para number='12'>
         Adventurers earn groats by doing Akaturi jobs - type 'HELP AKATURI'.
         </para>

      </section>

