         <para number='1' comment='warehouse/ware/depot/fetch/stor'>
         Merchants who have proved themselves can purchase warehouses to store goods in so they are not stolen from their ships at reset. See http://www.ibgames.net/fed2/guide/trading/ware.html for the requirements. Once you have a permit, go to an exchange and 'BUY WARE'.
         </para>

         <para number='2'>
         'STORE cargoname' moves the named cargo from your ship into the warehouse. 'DI WARE planetname' lists the contents of the warehouse, and 'FETCH #' moves the contents of the specified bay into your ship. 'SHUFFLE' moves all the goods to the lowest-numbered bays. Dispose of a warehouse with 'SELL WARE'. Traders can also sell warehouses, but not buy them. 'DI WARE' (without specifying a planet) lists all of your warehouses.
         </para>

         <para number='3'>
