   <category name='wear'>

      <section name='nothing'>

         <para number='1' comment='wear/carry/doff/pocket/clip/un'>
         There are three ways to display objects in your inventory, so that other players can see them when they examine you: you can wear them, carry them and clip them to your keyring. None of these actions have any effect on the use the objects have; it's just for display purposes.
         </para>

         <para number='2' comment='wear'>
         The commands 'WEAR objectname' and 'CARRY objectname' display the specified objects. You can wear and carry as many objects as you like. Reverse it with 'DOFF objectname' and 'POCKET objectname'.
         </para>

         <para number='3'>
         To attach an object to your keyring, use 'CLIP objectname'. You can only have one object at a time dangling from the keyring. Remove the object with 'UNCLIP'.
         </para>

         <para number='4'>
         The keyrings themselves are available from the high-class store Gallagher's on Earth, for one slithy tove each. They are intended to display the charms, also on sale at Gallagher's, although you can clip any object to them. They also come with the key to the executive washroom.
         </para>

         <para number='5'>
         Note that when visiting Pearl, you are expected to comply with the local customs, one of which is that visitors should wear the special slippers called tabi. When you are given a pair, type 'WEAR TABI' and you will be allowed to proceed.
